DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260622
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260623
SUMMARY:Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM
DESCRIPTION:Start your week with a primary double kettlebell EMOM. Focus on maintaining 8 good reps as your baseline. Optional: Start with 20 minutes.\n# Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `20-30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `double kettlebells`\n\n## Summary\n\nDouble-kettlebell EMOM built around the core power and strength patterns.\n\n## Work\n\n- Swings\n- Squats\n- Cleans\n- Presses\n- Rows\n\n# Notes\n\n- Start with 12-16 kg and 6-8 reps for 20 minutes.\n- Work up to 10 swings.\n- Increase duration toward 30 minutes\, dropping reps as needed.\n- Once you can hold 10 reps for 30 minutes across the board\, repeat at a heavier weight.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/YVSWjN7CPFo?lc=UgxfFSvUIMg61ILclJd4AaABAg&si=L4rxxK4HUzv0h9j8\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-02@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260623
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260624
SUMMARY:Daily Mobility Routine
DESCRIPTION:Quick full-body mobility to support recovery. Stack this short session with the next session if preferred.\n# Daily Mobility Routine\n\n- Domain: `mobility`\n- Session Duration: `5 min total`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Format: `30 secs each`\n- Equipment: `none`\n\n## Summary\n\nFull-body mobility circuit with a short hold or flow at each station.\n\n## Work\n\n- Twists\n- Arm Circles\n- Aura Farmers\n- Chiropractors\n- Body Waves\n- MacGregors\n- Side Bends\n- Lunge Reaches\n- Monk Squats\n- Cossack Squats\n\n## Notes\n\n- Move for 30 seconds at each drill.\n- Keep the total session to about 5 minutes.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/A39EAsO-0v0?si=msiPl3A_5wiJOwsr\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-03@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260624
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260625
SUMMARY:Push Up EMOM 10 Min
DESCRIPTION:First push-up EMOM for the week. Target your current sustainable rep count per minute for 10 minutes. No kettlebells today.\n# Push Up EMOM 10 Min\n\n- Domain: `bodyweight`\n- Session Duration: `10 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-4x/week`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `none`\n\n## Summary\n\nProgressive push-up EMOM built around a sustainable rep target that you can repeat every minute for 10 minutes.\n\n## Work\n\n- Pick a push-up number you can complete every minute on the minute for 10 minutes.\n- Example: 5 push-ups per minute for 10 minutes = 50 total push-ups.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Try to increase the rep target every few weeks.\n- Repeat this workout consistently 2-4 times per week.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-04@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260625
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260626
SUMMARY:Kettlebell 30 Min
DESCRIPTION:Primary single kettlebell circuit. Perform as many quality rounds as possible in 30 minutes. Prioritize movement quality.\n# Kettlebell 30 Min\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `AMRAP`\n- Equipment: `kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nSingle-kettlebell conditioning circuit with swings\, squats\, presses\, rows\, and push-ups.\n\n## Work\n\n- 10 swings\n- 5 squats\, weight on one side\n- 5 shoulder presses each side\n- 5 rows each side\n- Push ups (50% max)\n\n## Notes\n\n- Perform as many quality rounds as possible in 30 minutes.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-05@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260626
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260627
SUMMARY:Suitcase Carry
DESCRIPTION:Complete the 1 mile suitcase carry challenge. Use good posture and switch arms often.\n# Suitcase Carry\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `~20-25 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-3x/week`\n- Format: `carry`\n- Equipment: `single kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nLoaded carry performed one arm at a time in a suitcase hold\, alternating sides periodically.\n\n## Work\n\n- Carry a single kettlebell for one mile.\n- Use a suitcase hold.\n- Switch arms periodically.\n- Try not to put the bell down.\n- If needed\, perform a single-arm deadlift to switch arms.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use a kettlebell around 20-30% of body weight.\n- Keep posture tall and controlled throughout the carry.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-06@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260627
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260628
SUMMARY:The Stack: Foundation
DESCRIPTION:First swing speed session. Use The Stack Foundation protocol as prescribed.\n# The Stack: Foundation\n\n- Domain: `swing-speed`\n- Session Duration: `~25 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Program: `18 sessions total\, ~6 weeks`\n- Format: `program`\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Foundation is the meat-and-potatoes speed training program. It is designed to ease a beginner into speed training and has consistently delivered gains across golfers with different levels of experience.\n\n## Work\n\n- Use The Stack app to continue the program.\n- Spend about 10 minutes on the warmup.\n- Complete 3-4 intervals of 4-8 swings at different weights.\n\n## Notes\n\n- This program is commonly repeated.\n- The full run takes approximately 6 weeks to complete.\n- The session itself is roughly 25 minutes.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-07@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260628
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260629
SUMMARY:Hip Mobility
DESCRIPTION:Dedicated hip recovery and mobility. Use this to prep or recover from loaded work.\n# Hip Mobility\n\n- Domain: `mobility`\n- Session Duration: `not specified`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Format: `mobility circuit`\n- Equipment: `bodyweight`\n\n## Summary\n\nHip-focused mobility and activation sequence with gait\, squat\, and balance drills.\n\n## Work\n\n- Hydrants\n- Hip Circles\n- Heel Kicks\n- Straight Leg Kicks (back\, then side)\n- 90/90s\n- Foot roll outs\n- Heel toe walk\n- A Skips\n- C Skips\n- Side Lunges\n- Squat twists\n- Pogos\n- Rotational Bounds\n- Crossovers (Slow/Fasts)\n- Front Squats\n- 90/90s\n- DB Hip Holds\n- Cossack Squats\n- Deadbugs\n- SL Calf Raises\n- Bigeon Reach\n- SL Glute Bridge\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use this as a prep or recovery session for hips and lower body.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/AIMawvpT0tE?si=FFWj6JcDn5BRQ-Lo\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-08@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260629
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260630
SUMMARY:Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM
DESCRIPTION:Continue progression with the primary double KB EMOM. Do not go more than 2 days in a row for kettlebell primaries.\n# Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `20-30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `double kettlebells`\n\n## Summary\n\nDouble-kettlebell EMOM built around the core power and strength patterns.\n\n## Work\n\n- Swings\n- Squats\n- Cleans\n- Presses\n- Rows\n\n# Notes\n\n- Start with 12-16 kg and 6-8 reps for 20 minutes.\n- Work up to 10 swings.\n- Increase duration toward 30 minutes\, dropping reps as needed.\n- Once you can hold 10 reps for 30 minutes across the board\, repeat at a heavier weight.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/YVSWjN7CPFo?lc=UgxfFSvUIMg61ILclJd4AaABAg&si=L4rxxK4HUzv0h9j8\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-09@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Project 120 - Bands Weekday 1
DESCRIPTION:Swing-speed support work for rotation and power with band holds.\n# Project 120 - Bands Weekday 1\n\n- Domain: `swing-speed`\n- Session Duration: `not specified`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Format: `band work`\n- Equipment: `resistance bands`\n\n## Summary\n\nBand-based golf swing speed support work emphasizing positions through the swing.\n\n## Work\n\n- 3 x 10 sec holds top of backswing (both sides red band)\n- 3 x 10 sec holds halfway swing (both sides red band)\n- 3 x 10 sec holds impact (both sides red band)\n- 10 x lat pull down reps (red & yellow bands)\n- 3 x 10 second lead leg cross both legs (yellow band)\n- 3 x 10 second trail leg cross both legs (yellow band)\n\n## Notes\n\n- Work both sides where noted.\n
END:VEVENT
