SUMMARY:Kettlebell 30 Min
DESCRIPTION:Primary single KB circuit\; keep pace steady—quality matters over total rounds.\n# Kettlebell 30 Min\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `AMRAP`\n- Equipment: `kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nSingle-kettlebell conditioning circuit with swings\, squats\, presses\, rows\, and push-ups.\n\n## Work\n\n- 10 swings\n- 5 squats\, weight on one side\n- 5 shoulder presses each side\n- 5 rows each side\n- Push ups (50% max)\n\n## Notes\n\n- Perform as many quality rounds as possible in 30 minutes.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-32@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260723
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260724
SUMMARY:Push Up EMOM 10 Min
DESCRIPTION:Push-up EMOM\, not after a KB day with push-ups. Focus on clean movement and full range.\n# Push Up EMOM 10 Min\n\n- Domain: `bodyweight`\n- Session Duration: `10 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-4x/week`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `none`\n\n## Summary\n\nProgressive push-up EMOM built around a sustainable rep target that you can repeat every minute for 10 minutes.\n\n## Work\n\n- Pick a push-up number you can complete every minute on the minute for 10 minutes.\n- Example: 5 push-ups per minute for 10 minutes = 50 total push-ups.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Try to increase the rep target every few weeks.\n- Repeat this workout consistently 2-4 times per week.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-33@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260724
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260725
SUMMARY:The Stack: Foundation
DESCRIPTION:End-of-block speed session. Try to beat previous averages on at least one phase.\n# The Stack: Foundation\n\n- Domain: `swing-speed`\n- Session Duration: `~25 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Program: `18 sessions total\, ~6 weeks`\n- Format: `program`\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Foundation is the meat-and-potatoes speed training program. It is designed to ease a beginner into speed training and has consistently delivered gains across golfers with different levels of experience.\n\n## Work\n\n- Use The Stack app to continue the program.\n- Spend about 10 minutes on the warmup.\n- Complete 3-4 intervals of 4-8 swings at different weights.\n\n## Notes\n\n- This program is commonly repeated.\n- The full run takes approximately 6 weeks to complete.\n- The session itself is roughly 25 minutes.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e0941306da7-34@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260628T135842Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260725
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260726
SUMMARY:Golf Mobility Warmup
DESCRIPTION:Finish strong with golf-specific prep/warmup. Use before practice or as dedicated mobility.\n# Golf Mobility Warmup\n\n- Domain: `mobility`\n- Session Duration: `not specified`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Format: `warmup circuit`\n- Equipment: `bodyweight`\, `optional implements`\n\n## Summary\n\nGolf-specific mobility and prep sequence covering trunk rotation\, locomotion\, and power patterns.\n\n## Work\n\n- Forward Lunges (Overhead\, Side Bend\, Rotation)\n- Glute Bridges (Double\, Single leg)\n- Bird Dogs\n- T-spine Rotations\n- Cat Cow\n- Bear Walk\n- 90/90s\n- Tactical Frogs\n- Half Frogs with Rotation\n- Pushup w/ Downward Dog\n- World's Greatest Stretch\n- X-Factor\n- Lateral Lunge w Rotations\n- Weighted Lateral Lunges\n- Lateral Bounds\n- Rotational Box Jumps\n- KB Carries\n- Single Leg Deadlift\n- Side Planks\n- Kopenhagen Side Planks\n- Med Ball Throws Down\n- Med Ball Chest Pass\n- Cable Pushes\n- Cable Rows\n- Squat Row\n\n## Notes\n\n- Choose the drills that best fit the session or stack them into a longer warmup.\n
END:VEVENT
